<body>
    <h1>1- PB Rebates, Schemes and Price difference- Ops process SOP</h1>
    <div class=3D"Section1">
        <h2 id=3D"id-1-PBRebates,SchemesandPricedifference-OpsprocessSOP-Pu=
rposeandScope"><strong>Purpose and Scope</strong></h2>
<p>To align, manage and track influencer meets across distributor and retai=
ler locations, in order to educate and onboard potential partners and incre=
ase sales reach.</p>
<p><strong>Handover timeline: PB -&gt;BizOps: </strong>8-30 September 2025<=
/p>
<h2 id=3D"id-1-PBRebates,SchemesandPricedifference-OpsprocessSOP-Stakeholde=
rs"><strong>Stakeholders</strong></h2>
<p>Primary data for Schemes, Rebates and Pricing cashbacks - Kunal Jani (PB=
 HO team)</p>
<p>Data entry and calculations - BizOps</p>
<p>Data management platform - Excel</p>
<p>CN issuance - <em>Responsibility to be distributed/aligned between BizOp=
s and Finance</em></p>
<p></p>
<h3 id=3D"id-1-PBRebates,SchemesandPricedifference-OpsprocessSOP-Pre-requis=
itesandkeypointstonote:"><strong>Pre-requisites and key points to note:</st=
rong></h3>
<ol start=3D"1">
<li>
<p>PB Sales team to share all types of schemes and rebates details with Biz=
Ops team on a monthly basis.</p></li>
<li>
<p>Schemes run at an order level and pricing at which CN will be raised is =
considered of the initial order date. For cases where there are Re-SLOs, th=
e pricing will still be considered from the original SLO date, which needs =
to be tracked manually in coordination with Sales.</p></li>
<li>
<p>Distributor and Dealer schemes and pricing are different, and decided by=
 PB Sales teams only.</p></li>
<li>
<p>Types of schemes: <em>*seperate CNs are created for each type of scheme =
below</em></p>
<ol start=3D"1">
<li>
<p>Additional/Normal support - Rs/MT</p></li>
<li>
<p>State level support - Rs/MT</p></li>
</ol></li>
<li>
<p>Additional schemes as and when introduced, to be shared by PB team to Bi=
zOps</p></li>
</ol>
<h2 id=3D"id-1-PBRebates,SchemesandPricedifference-OpsprocessSOP-Process"><=
strong>Process</strong></h2>
<p><strong>Rebates and Schemes CNs</strong></p>
<ol start=3D"1">
<li>
<p>BizOps to pick a scheme shared by PB team and refer the sheet <a class=
=3D"external-link" href=3D"https://jsw-my.sharepoint.com/:x:/r/personal/kun=
al_jani_jsw_in/_layouts/15/Doc.aspx?sourcedoc=3D%7BE552EFC9-240E-43C4-B083-=
28F7D9B4A260%7D&amp;file=3DFY%2026_Rebates%20&amp;%20Schemes%20working.xlsx=
=3D&amp;fromShare=3Dtrue&amp;action=3Ddefault&amp;mobileredirect=3Dtrue" re=
l=3D"nofollow">FY 26_Rebates &amp; Schemes working</a> for working and calc=
ulation.</p></li>
<li>
<p>User to update the scheme price state-wise in the top most section in th=
e tab under =E2=80=98State Supply=E2=80=99 and =E2=80=98State=E2=80=99</p><=
/li>
<li>
<p>Next, refer tab '&lt;month&gt;_state supply+add. supp.' and select Distr=
ibutor/Dealer name and Order date from the columns already auto-populating =
in the sheet.</p></li>
<li>
<p>Once the state-wise price is updated, similar column =E2=80=98State Supp=
ly=E2=80=99 in the table below will auto-populate rows with the price as me=
ntioned in point 2.</p></li>
<li>
<p>User to then manually add Additional support rebate price at the distrib=
utor and state level.</p></li>
<li>
<p>Once both =E2=80=98State supply=E2=80=99 and =E2=80=98Additional support=
 rebate=E2=80=99 price are added, it will calcuate total amount of both bas=
is the invoiced quantity already mentioned in the table againt the distribu=
tor/dealer.</p></li>
<li>
<p>Same process from 1-&gt;6 is to be repeated for all distributors/dealers=
 for order placed and fulfilled during the defined period/month.</p></li>
<li>
<p>Once done, the calculation needs to be shared with PB team for verificat=
ion. In case of an error or exception, BizOps to update calculations as per=
 feedback and share. <em>*exception workflow yet to be discussed.</em></p><=
/li>
<li>
<p>Once verified by PB team, BizOps to share details/file with PB finance f=
or further verification and respective approvals.</p></li>
<li>
<p>Once approved, a Credit Note is to be created for each distributor, sche=
me-wise in Zoho Books. <em>(ownership b/w BizOps and Finance teams yet to b=
e finalized):</em></p>
<ol start=3D"1">
<li>
<p><em>Finance to create, approve and email CNs to the distributors.</em></=
p></li>
<li>
<p><em>BizOps to create, approve and email CNs to the distributors.</em></p=
></li>
<li>
<p><em>BizOps to create CNs, Finance to approve and email to distributors.<=
/em></p></li>
</ol></li>
</ol>
<p></p>
<p><strong>Price Difference CNs</strong></p>
<ol start=3D"1">
<li>
<p>PB team to share price type: FOR ro Ex-works, and amount for each Distri=
butor at an order and dia level to BizOps.</p></li>
<li>
<p>BizOps to refer sheet <a class=3D"external-link" href=3D"https://jsw-my.=
sharepoint.com/:x:/r/personal/kunal_jani_jsw_in/_layouts/15/Doc.aspx?source=
doc=3D%7BA82E6FFD-CEA6-4265-87F1-E00531B38E1B%7D&amp;file=3DPrice%20differe=
nce%20calculations%20-%20May%2025.xlsx&amp;action=3Ddefault&amp;mobileredir=
ect=3Dtrue" rel=3D"nofollow">Price difference calculations</a> and check li=
st price, proposed price, FOR freight (if applicable) calculate difference =
in plant price vs proposed price.<em>*FOR prices can change month-on-month.=
</em></p></li>
<li>
<p>User to calculate CN value for each Distributor and share the working wi=
th PB and Finance team as in the above section.</p></li>
<li>
<p>Once approved, CN to be created as per the steps decided in point '10' o=
f the above section.</p></li>
</ol>
<p><strong>Consistency scheme (other)</strong></p>
<p>Sheet- <a class=3D"external-link" href=3D"https://jsw-my.sharepoint.com/=
:x:/r/personal/kunal_jani_jsw_in/_layouts/15/Doc.aspx?sourcedoc=3D%7B2499F8=
29-6249-4C64-B2C6-B8778E7E318C%7D&amp;file=3DFY%2026%20Q1%20consistency%20s=
cheme.xlsx&amp;fromShare=3Dtrue&amp;action=3Ddefault&amp;mobileredirect=3Dt=
rue" rel=3D"nofollow">FY 26 Q1 consistency scheme</a></p>
<ol start=3D"1">
<li>
<p>Dealers are segmented into categories basis the tonnage lifted each mont=
h.</p></li>
<li>
<p>Consistency scheme for Retailers is update by PB team and shared to BizO=
ps.</p></li>
<li>
<p>There are 2 types of schemes:</p>
<ol start=3D"1">
<li>
<p>Monthly scheme basis MOQ</p></li>
<li>
<p>Quarterly consistency scheme <em>(over and above monthly MOQ scheme)</em=
></p></li>
</ol></li>
<li>
<p>CN is to be issued separately for both schemes even if for the same Deal=
er.</p></li>
<li>
<p>CN issued should be in the name of Distributor, not dealer.</p></li>
</ol>
<h2 id=3D"id-1-PBRebates,SchemesandPricedifference-OpsprocessSOP-Timelines:=
